{"parse":{"title":"pasta","pageid":44974,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"{{also|Pasta|pastá|pastā|pastă|pastą|påstå}}\n{{minitoc}}\n==English==\n{{wp}}\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|en|a=UK|/ˈpæs.tə/}}\n** {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Vealhurl-pasta.wav|a=Southern England}}\n** {{IPA|en|aa=RP|[ˈpʰæstə]}}\n** {{IPA|en|aa=SSB|[ˈpʰastə]}}\n** {{IPA|en|[ˈp(ʰ)astə]|aa=Northern England,Wales,Scotland,Ireland}}\n\n* {{IPA|en|a=US|/ˈpɑ.stə/}}\n** {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Naomi Persephone Amethyst (NaomiAmethyst)-pasta.wav|a=GA}}\n\n* {{IPA|en|a=Canada|/ˈpæs.tə/}}\n* {{IPA|en|a=Indic|/ˈpɑs.t̪ɑ/|[päːst̪äˑ]}}\n* {{IPA|en|a=Philippines|[pɐːst̪ɐː]}}\n* {{IPA|en|a=AU|/ˈpɑː.stə/|[ˈpʰɐːstə]}}\n* {{IPA|en|a=NZ|/ˈpɑː.stə/|[ˈpʰɐːstɘ]|;|/ˈpæs.tə/<q:broad>|[ˈpʰɛstɘ]}}\n\n* {{hmp|en|pastor|aa=Australia,New Zealand,Northern England,non-rhotic}}\n* {{rhymes|en|æstə|ɑːstə||s=2}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\n{{etymon|en|id=food|:bor|it:pasta<id:food>|tree=1}}\nBorrowed from {{bor|en|it|pasta||paste; pasta, noodles}}, from {{der|en|la-lat|pasta|t=dough, pastry cake, paste}}, from {{der|en|grc|παστά|t=barley porridge}}, neuter plural of {{m|grc|παστός|t=sprinkled with salt}}, from {{der|en|grc|πάσσω||to sprinkle}}. {{doublet|en|paste}}.\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun|~|s|paste<id:pasta><l:rare>}}\n\n# {{lb|en|uncountable}} {{cap|dough}} made from [[wheat]] and water and sometimes mixed with [[egg]] and formed into various shapes; often sold in [[dried]] form and typically boiled for eating.\n#: {{syn|en|Thesaurus:pasta}}\n#: {{hyponyms|en|macaroni}}\n## {{lb|en|loosely}} Any type of [[noodle]].\n# {{lb|en|uncountable}} A [[dish]] or [[serving]] of pasta.\n# {{lb|en|countable}} A [[type]] of pasta.\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col|en\n|copypasta\n|egg pasta\n|hasta la pasta\n|hasta pasta\n|impasta\n|nanopasta\n|nonpasta\n|nuclear pasta\n|pasta bake\n|pasta basica\n|pasta e fagioli\n|Pastafarian\n|Pastafarianism\n|pasta fazool\n|Pastagate\n|pastaholic\n|pastalaya\n|pastaless\n|pastalike\n|pasta salad\n|pasta sauce\n|pasta wheat\n}}\n\n=====Related terms=====\n{{col|en\n|pasta filata\n|paste\n|pâté\n|pate\n|patty\n}}\n\n=====Descendants=====\n{{top3}}\n* {{desc|id|pasta|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|hi|पास्ता|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|mr|पास्ता|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|th|พาสตา|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|cy|pasta|bor=1}}\n{{bottom}}\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{trans-top|dough}}{{multitrans|data=\n* Albanian: {{t+|sq|makarona|f-p|alt=makaronat}}, {{t|sq|pasta|f}}\n* Arabic: {{t+|ar|مَكَرُونَة|f}}, {{t+|ar|مَعْكَرُونَة|f}}, {{t|ar|بَاسْتَا|f}}\n*: Algerian Arabic: {{tt|arq|ماقرونة}}\n*: Gulf Arabic: {{t|afb|معكرونية|tr=maʕkarōnya}}\n*: Hijazi Arabic: {{tt|acw|مَكَرُونَة|f|tr=makarōna}}\n*: Moroccan Arabic: {{tt|ary|مقرونية|f|tr=maqarūniyya}}\n* Armenian: {{t+|hy|մակարոնեղեն}} {{q|collective}}, {{t+|hy|մակարոն}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{t|az|makaron}}\n* Basque: {{t+|eu|pasta}}\n* Belarusian: {{t|be|макаро́нныя вы́рабы|m-p}}, {{t|be|макаро́ны|p}}\n* Bengali: {{t+|bn|পাস্তা}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t|bg|па́ста|f}}\n* Burmese: {{t|my|ပါစတာ}}\n* Catalan: {{tt+|ca|pasta|f}}\n* Cebuano: {{tt|ceb|pasta}}\n* Chechen: {{t|ce|гарзнаш|p}}, {{t|ce|гарз}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Cantonese: {{tt|yue|意大利粉}}, {{tt|yue|意粉}} {{q|abbreviation}}\n*: Dungan: {{tt|dng|мянфан}}\n*: Mandarin: {{tt+|cmn|意大利麵}}\n* Czech: {{tt+|cs|těstoviny|f-p}}\n* Danish: {{tt+|da|pasta|c}}\n* Dutch: {{tt+|nl|deegwaren|f-p}}, {{t+|nl|pasta|m}}\n* Esperanto: {{tt+|eo|pasto}}\n* Estonian: {{t+|et|pasta}}\n* Faroese: {{tt|fo|pasta|f}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|pasta}}\n* French: {{tt+|fr|pâtes|f-p}}, {{tt+|fr|pâtes alimentaires|f-p}}\n* Georgian: {{t|ka|მაკარონის ნაწარმი}}, {{t|ka|მაკარონი}}\n* German: {{tt+|de|Nudeln|f-p}}; {{q|formal|specialist}} {{tt+|de|Teigwaren|f-p}}; {{q|commercial sometimes}} {{tt+|de|Pasta|f}}\n* Greek: {{tt+|el|ζυμαρικά|n-p}}\n*: Ancient Greek: {{tt|grc|κολλύρα|f}}\n* Hebrew: {{tt+|he|פַּסְטָה|f|tr=pásta}}\n* Hindi: {{tt|hi|पास्ता|m}}\n* Hungarian: {{tt+|hu|tészta}}\n* Hunsrik: {{tt|hrx|Nutle|f-p}}\n* Icelandic: {{tt+|is|pasta|n}}\n* Indonesian: {{t+|id|pasta}}\n* Irish: {{tt|ga|pasta|m}}\n* Italian: {{tt+|it|pasta|f}}, {{tt+|it|impasto|m}}\n* Japanese: {{tt+|ja|パスタ|tr=pasuta}}\n* Kazakh: {{t|kk|макарон}}\n* Khmer: {{t|km|ប៉ាស្តា}}\n* Korean: {{tt+|ko|파스타}}\n* Kurdish:\n*: Northern Kurdish: {{tt|kmr|meqarne}}\n* Kyrgyz: {{t|ky|макарон}}\n* Lao: {{t|lo|ພາສຕ້າ}}\n* Latin: {{tt|la|collȳra|f}}, {{tt|la|pasta|f}} {{q|Late}}\n* Latvian: {{t|lv|pasta|f}}\n* Lithuanian: {{tt|lt|makaronas|m}}, {{tt|lt|makaronai|m-p}}\n* Macedonian: {{tt|mk|тестенина|f}}\n* Malay: {{t|ms|pasta}}\n* Marathi: {{tt|mr|पास्ता|m}}, {{t|mr|पास्ता|m}}\n* Mòcheno: {{tt|mhn|pasta|f}}\n* Norman: {{tt|nrf|pâtes|f-p}} {{q|Jersey}}\n* Norwegian:\n*: Bokmål: {{tt+|nb|pasta|m}}\n* Persian:\n*: Iranian Persian: {{tt|fa-ira|پاسْتا}}\n* Polish: {{tt+|pl|makaron|m}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt+|pt|massa|f}}, {{q|Brazil}} {{tt+|pt|macarrão|m}}\n* Romanian: {{tt+|ro|paste făinoase|f-p}}\n* Russian: {{tt+|ru|макаро́ны|p}}, {{tt|ru|макаро́нные изде́лия|n-p}}, {{q|slang}} {{tt+|ru|па́ста|f}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{tt|sh|тестенѝна|f}}, {{tt|sh|тјестенѝна|f}}, {{t|sh|па̏ста|f}}\n*: Latin: {{tt|sh|testenìna|f}}, {{tt+|sh|tjestenìna|f}}, {{t+|sh|pȁsta|f}}\n* Slovak: {{tt|sk|cestovina|f}}\n* Slovene: {{t|sl|testenina|f}}\n* Spanish: {{tt+|es|pasta|f}}\n* Swedish: {{tt+|sv|pasta|c}}\n* Tagalog: {{tt|tl|pasta}}\n* Tajik: {{t|tg|макарон}}\n* Tamil: {{tt|ta|மாச்சேவை}}\n* Thai: {{tt|th|พาสตา}}\n* Turkish: {{tt+|tr|makarna}}\n* Turkmen: {{t|tk|makaron}}\n* Ukrainian: {{tt|uk|макаро́нні ви́роби|m-p}}, {{t|uk|макаро́ни|p}}\n* Urdu: {{t|ur|پاسْتا|m}}\n* Uzbek: {{t+|uz|makaron}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t|vi|mì ống}}\n* Welsh: {{tt+|cy|pasta|m}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|dish or serving}}\n* Arabic:\n*: Moroccan Arabic: {{tt|ary|مقرونية|f|tr=maqarūniyya}}\n* Chechen: {{t|ce|гарзнаш}}\n* Finnish: {{tt|fi|pastaruoka}} {{q|dish}}; {{tt|fi|[[pasta]]-[[annos]]}} {{q|serving}}\n* German: {{tt+|de|Nudeln|f-p}}; {{tt+|de|Nudelgericht|n}}\n* Hebrew: {{tt+|he|פַּסְטָה|f|tr=pásta}}\n* Marathi: {{t|mr|पास्ता|m}}\n* Thai: {{tt|th|พาสตา}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|type of pasta}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{tt+|cmn|意大利麵}}\n* Finnish: {{tt|fi|pastalaji}}\n* Marathi: {{t|mr|पास्ता|m}}\n* Thai: {{tt|th|พาสตา}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-see|any type of noodle|noodle}}\n}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\n{{etymon|en|:clip|copypasta<id:block of text>|tree=1|id=block of text}}\n{{clip|en|copypasta}}.\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# A [[copypasta]] {{gl|block of text which has been [[copy-paste|copied and paste]]d from somewhere else, serving as a [[story]] or [[meme]]}}.\n\n===Etymology 3===\n{{etymon|en|id=dental|:bor|es-PH:pasta<id:paste>|tree=1}}\n{{bor+|en|es-PH|pasta}}, from {{der|en|la-lat|pasta|t=dough, pastry cake, paste}}, from {{der|en|grc|παστά|t=barley porridge}}.\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun|~|s}}\n\n# {{lb|en|Philippines|dentistry|countable|uncountable}} {{cap|dental}} [[filling]].\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=aapst|ataps|patas|tapas}}\n\n{{C|en|Foods}}\n\n==Catalan==\n\n===Etymology 1===\n{{inh+|ca|la-lat|pasta}}, from {{der|ca|grc|παστά}}.\n\n====Pronunciation====\n* {{ca-IPA}}\n* {{audio|ca|LL-Q7026 (cat)-Marvives-pasta.wav|a=Catalonia}}\n\n====Noun====\n{{ca-noun|f}}\n\n# [[paste]], [[putty]]\n# [[pulp]] {{q|for papermaking}}\n# [[dough]]\n# {{l|en|pasta}} {{gloss|dough made from wheat and water}}\n# {{lb|ca|colloquial}} [[money]], [[dough]]\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col3|ca|empastar|empastifar|pasta de dents|pasta d'ebenista|pasta de te|pasta fullada|pastar|pastetes|pastís}}\n\n====References====\n* {{R:ca:IEC2}}\n* {{R:ca:GDLC}}\n* {{R:ca:DNV}}\n* {{R:ca:DCVB}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\n\n====Verb====\n{{head|ca|verb form}}\n\n# {{ca-verb form of|pastar}}\n\n{{cln|ca|terms inherited from Latin}}\n\n==Cebuano==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{hyphenation|ceb|pas|ta}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\nBorrowed from Spanish pasta.\n\n====Noun====\n{{head|ceb|noun}}\n\n# [[dental]] [[filling]]\n\n===Etymology 2===\nBorrowed from {{bor|ceb|es|pasta}},\nborrowed from {{der|ceb|it|pasta}}, from {{der|ceb|la-lat|pasta|t=dough, pastry cake, paste}}, from {{der|ceb|grc|παστά|t=barley porridge}}, from {{m|grc|παστός|t=sprinkled with salt}}.\n\n====Noun====\n{{head|ceb|noun}}\n\n# {{l|en|pasta}}\n## [[dough]] made from [[wheat]] and water and sometimes mixed with [[egg]] and formed into various shapes; often sold in [[dried]] form and typically boiled for eating\n## a [[dish]] or [[serving]] of pasta\n## a [[type]] of pasta\n\n{{C|ceb|Dentistry}}\n\n==Central Bikol==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{bor+|bcl|es|pasta}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{bcl-IPA}}\n* {{hyph|bcl|pas|ta}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{bcl-noun|pásta|b=+}}\n\n# [[paste]]\n#: {{syn|bcl|pulot}}\n# {{lb|bcl|dentistry}} [[filling]]\n#: {{syn|bcl|semento}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col3|bcl|magpasta|ipasta|pastahan}}\n\n==Cimbrian==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{bor|cim|it|pasta}}, from {{der|cim|la-lat|pasta}}, from {{der|cim|grc|παστά}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{cim-noun|f}}\n\n# {{lb|cim|Luserna}} [[#English|pasta]]\n\n===References===\n* {{R:Patuzzi}}\n\n{{c|cim|Foods}}\n\n==Czech==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{bor+|cs|la-lat|pasta}}; cf. {{cog|it|pasta}}, {{cog|en|paste}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{cs-IPA}}\n* {{audio|cs|Cs-pasta.ogg}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{cs-noun|f}}\n\n# [[paste]]\n\n====Declension====\n{{cs-ndecl|f}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|cs|zubní pasta}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:cs:PSJC}}\n* {{R:cs:SSJC}}\n* {{R:cs:IJP}}\n\n==Danish==\n{{wp|da:}}\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{der|da|it|pasta}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|da|/ˈpasda/|[ˈpʰæsd̥æ]|[ˈpʰæstæ]}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{da-noun|en|er}}\n\n# {{l|en|pasta}} {{q|food}}\n# [[paste]]\n\n====Declension====\n{{da-decl|en|er}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col4|da\n|pastaret\n|pastasalat\n|pastaskrue\n|tandpasta\n|pastaopskrift\n|pastaproduktion\n|pastamager\n|pastafabrik\n|pastadej\n|pastaprodukt\n|fuldkornspasta\n|pastavare\n|pastastykke\n|pastarør\n|pastakuvert\n|pastaform\n|pastafabrikant\n|pastakogebog\n}}\n\n====See also====\n* {{l|da|makaroni}}\n* {{l|da|nudel}}\n* {{l|da|spaghetti}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:DDO}}\n\n{{C|da|Foods}}\n\n==Dutch==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|nl|/ˈpɑs.taː/}}\n* {{hyphenation|nl|pas|ta}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\n{{lbor|nl|la-lat|pasta||dough, paste}}, from {{der|nl|grc|παστά|t=barley porridge}}. Displaced {{m|nl|paste}}.\n\n====Noun====\n{{nl-noun|f|-'s|+}}\n\n# [[paste]] {{defdate|from late 16th c.}}\n#* '''1596''', Jan Huyghen van Linschoten, ''Itinerario, voyage ofte schipvaert naer Oost ofte Portugaels Indien 1579-1592'', part 2, publ. by Martinus Nijhoff (1956), page 147.\n#*: {{quote|nl|Het eerste noemen die AEgyptenaren assis, 'twelc is poyer van kennep ofte hennep bladeren, met water tot een '''pasta''' ofte deegh ghemaect, daer af zy vijf ofte meer stucxkens eten, so groot als castanien, van 't vvelcke de ghene, die sulcks ghegheten hebben, een ure daernae niet anders worden dan of zy droncken waren, met ontsinnigheyt; worden van selfs gelijc oft zy opgetrocken waren, ende haer verschynen vremde ghesichten, daer in zy groote vermakelickheyt hebben.|The first one the Egyptians call hashish, which is a powder of cannabis or hemp leaves, made into a '''paste''' or dough with water, of which they eat five or more pieces as big as chestnuts, from which those who have eaten such, become for an hour thereafter nothing but as if they were drunk, with senselessness; [they] become on their own as if they are in an exalted state, and strange visions appear to them, in which they have great amusement.}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n* {{l|nl|chocoladepasta}}\n* {{l|nl|hazelnootpasta}}\n* {{l|nl|pastavreter}}\n* {{l|nl|tandpasta}}\n\n=====Descendants=====\n* {{desc|af|pasta}}\n* {{desc|id|pasta|bor=1}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\nBorrowed from {{bor|nl|it|pasta}}, from {{der|nl|la-lat|pasta}}, from {{der|nl|grc|παστά}}.\n\n====Noun====\n{{nl-noun|f|-'s|+}}\n\n# {{l|en|pasta}} {{defdate|from mid 19th c.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|nl|year=1866|author=S. J. van den Bergh|title=Een Engelschman onder de roovers|journal=De Gids|volume=30|page=334\n|passage=Een groot vuur brandde lustig onder een ketel gevuld met '''pasta''', eene soort van macaroni, waarboven gansche brokken sneeuw werden gesmolten die met een overvloed van warme geitenmelk, ons tot drank verstrekten.|t=A large fire burned eagerly under a cauldron filled with '''pasta''', a type of macaroni, above which entire chunks of snow were molten that served us as a beverage [together] with an abundance of warm goat milk.}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n* {{l|nl|pastamachine}}\n* {{l|nl|pastasalade}}\n* {{l|nl|pastasaus}}\n* {{l|nl|pastavorm}}\n\n==Faroese==\n\n===Etymology===\nBorrowed from {{bor|fo|it|pasta}}, from {{der|fo|la-lat|pasta|t=dough, pastry cake, paste}}, from {{der|fo|grc|παστά|t=barley porridge}}, from {{m|grc|παστός|t=sprinkled with salt}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|fo|/ˈpʰasta/}}\n* {{rhymes|fo|asta}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{fo-noun|f|pastu|-}}\n\n# [[#English|pasta]]\n\n====Declension====\n{{fo-decl-noun-f1-s|past}}\n\n{{C|fo|Foods}}\n\n==Finnish==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{fi-pronunciation}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\n{{etymid|fi|food}}\n[[File:Pasta Carbonara at Gete Deli in May 2024 close up.jpg|thumb|Pasta dish (rigatoni alla carbonara)]]\nBorrowed from {{bor|fi|it|pasta}}.\n\n====Noun====\n{{fi-noun}}\n\n# [[#English|pasta]] {{gl|food}}\n\n=====Declension=====\n{{fi-decl-kala|past|||a}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col|fi\n|pastafarismi\n}}\n\n{{col|fi|title=compounds\n|broileripasta\n|kasvispasta\n|kierrepasta\n|kuivapasta\n|lohipasta\n|munapasta\n|nauhapasta\n|pastakastike\n|pastakauha\n|pastakone\n|pastaruoka\n|pastasalaatti\n|pastasiivilä\n|pastataikina\n|pastavehnä\n|pastavuoka\n|pekonipasta\n|pennepasta\n|perhospasta\n|putkipasta\n|ruispasta\n|tuorepasta\n}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\n{{etymid|fi|paste}}\nFrom {{der|fi|la-lat|pasta}}.\n\n====Noun====\n{{fi-noun}}\n\n# {{syn of|fi|tahna||paste}}\n\n=====Declension=====\n{{fi-decl-kala|past|||a}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col|fi|title=compounds\n|juotospasta\n|pastajuotos\n|sinkkipasta\n}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:fi:KTSK|accessdate=2024-01-01}} <!-- etymologies 1 and 2 -->\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|fi|a=aapst|Tapsa|tapas}}\n\n{{C|fi|Foods|Pasta}}\n\n==Galician==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{etydate|15th century}}. From {{der|gl|la|pasta}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{gl-pr}}\n* {{hyph|gl|pas|ta}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{gl-noun|f}}\n\n# [[paste]]\n#* {{quote-book|gl|year=1409|editor=G. Pérez Barcala|title=A tradución galega do \"Liber de medicina equorum\" de Joradanus Ruffus|location=Santiago de Compostela|publisher=USC|page=172|text=filla o vinagre ben forte e a greda alva muda et pouco de sal ben mundo, e amasa todo moi ben ata que se faça ende ũa '''pasta''' mole.|t=take a strong vinegar and ground white clay and a little salt, finely ground, and mix very well everything till it becames a soft '''paste'''}}\n# {{l|en|pasta}}\n# [[dough]]\n#: {{syn|gl|masa}}\n# [[binding]], [[cover]] of a [[book]]\n# {{lb|gl|slang}} [[money]], [[dough]]\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col3|gl|empastar}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:gl:DDLG}}\n* {{R:gl:TILG}}\n* {{R:TLPGP}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:gl:DRAG}}\n* {{R:gl:Estraviz}}\n\n==Icelandic==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{bor+|is|it|pasta}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|is|/ˈpʰasta/}}\n* {{rhymes|is|asta|s=2}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{is-noun|@@}}\n\n# {{l|en|pasta}}\n\n====Declension====\n{{is-ndecl|n.sg}}\n\n{{C|is|Foods}}\n\n==Indonesian==\n{{wp|id:}}\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{der|id|nl|pasta|t=pasta, paste}}, from {{der|id|la-lat|pasta||dough, pastry cake, paste}}, from {{der|id|grc|παστά||barley porridge}}, from {{m|grc|παστός||sprinkled with salt}}. {{doublet|id|pastel}}.\n* The sense of pasta is loaned via {{der|id|it|pasta}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{id-pr}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{id-noun|head=pásta}}\n\n# [[paste]]: a soft moist mixture\n# {{l|en|pasta}}:\n## dough made from wheat and water and sometimes mixed with egg and formed into various shapes; often sold in dried form and typically boiled for eating; a dish or serving of pasta\n## a type of pasta\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|id\n|berpasta\n}}\n{{col|id\n|pasta gigi\n}}\n\n====Related terms====\n{{col|id\n|pastel\n}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:KBBI Daring}}\n\n==Irish==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{bor|ga|en|pasta}}, from {{der|ga|it|pasta}}, from {{der|ga|la-lat|pasta||dough, pastry cake, paste}}, from {{der|ga|grc|παστά||barley porridge}}, from {{m|grc|παστός||sprinkled with salt}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|ga|/ˈpˠasˠt̪ˠə/}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{ga-noun|m|~|-}}\n\n# [[#English|pasta]]\n\n====Declension====\n{{ga-decl-m4-nopl|p|asta}}\n\n===Mutation===\n{{ga-mut}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:ga:NEID}}\n\n==Italian==\n{{wp|it:}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{etymon|it|id=food|:inh|la-lat:pasta<id:food>|tree=1}}\n{{inh+|it|la-lat|pasta}}, from {{der|it|grc|παστά}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{it-pr|pàsta}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{it-noun|f}}\n\n# [[paste]]\n# {{l|en|pasta}}, [[noodles]]\n# [[dough]]\n# [[cake]], [[tart]]\n# [[texture]]\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col4|it\n|pasta abrasiva\n|pasta alimentare\n|pasta all'uovo\n|pasta asciutta\n|pastasciutta\n|pasta brisée\n|pasta chimica\n|pasta cresciuta\n|pasta da carta\n|pasta di alluminio\n|pasta di fondo\n|pasta di legno\n|pasta di mandorle\n|pasta di paglia\n|pasta di stracci\n|pasta di vetro\n|pasta d'uomo\n|pasta dura\n|pasta fresca\n|pasta frolla|\n|pastafrolla\n|pasta glutinata\n|pasta margherita\n|pasta meccanica\n|pasta normale\n|pasticca\n}}\n\n====Descendants====\n{{top3}}\n* {{desc|aa|bastá|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ar|باستا||bor=1}}\n* {{desc|cim|pasta|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|da|pasta|bor=1}}\n* {{desctree|nl|pasta|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|en|pasta|bor=1}} {{see desc}}\n* {{desc|fo|pasta|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|fi|pasta|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|de|Pasta|bor=1}}\n* {{desctree|el|πάστα|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|is|pasta|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ja|パスタ|tr=pasuta|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ko|파스타|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|lld|pasta|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|mhn|pasta|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|no|-|bor=1}} {{l|nb|pasta}}\n* {{desc|fa|پاستا|tr=pâstâ|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|so|baasto|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|tr|pasta|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|fy|pasta|bor=1}}\n{{bottom}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|it|a=aapst|spata}}\n\n{{C|it|Foods}}\n\n==Latin==\n\n===Etymology 1===\n{{etymon|la|id=food|:bor|grc:παστά<id:porridge>}}\nBorrowed from {{bor|la|grc|παστά}}, from {{m|grc|παστός}}, from {{m|grc|πάσσω|t=sprinkle}}, from {{der|la|ine-pro|*kʷeh₁t-|t=to shake}}.\n\n====Pronunciation====\n* {{la-IPA|pasta}}\n\n====Noun====\n{{la-noun|pasta<1>}} {{lb|la|Late Latin}}\n\n# [[paste]]\n# {{lb|la|New Latin}} {{l|en|pasta}}\n\n=====Declension=====\n{{la-ndecl|pasta<1>}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n* {{l|la-vul|*pastīcius}}\n\n=====Descendants=====\n{{top3}}\n* Italo-Romance:\n** {{desc|it|pasta}} {{see desc}}\n** {{desc|scn|pasta}}\n* Padanian:\n** {{desc|vec|pasta}}\n* Northern Gallo-Romance:\n** {{desctree|fro|paste}}\n* Occitano-Romance:\n** {{desc|ca|pasta}}\n** {{desc|oc|pasta}}\n* Ibero-Romance:\n** {{desc|gl|pasta}}\n** {{desc|pt|pasta}}\n** {{desc|es|pasta}}\n{{bottom}}\n; \nUnsorted borrowings (many or all via French/Italian):\n{{top3}}\n* {{desc|be|паста|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|cs|pasta|bor=1}}\n* {{desctree|nl|pasta|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|fi|pasta|bor=1}}\n* {{desctree|de|Paste|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|hu|paszta|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|mk|паста|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|pl|pasta|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ru|паста|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|sh|pasta|bor=1}} / {{l|sh|паста}}\n* {{desc|sk|pasta|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|uk|паста|bor=1}}\n{{bottom}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\n{{nonlemma}}\n\n====Pronunciation====\n* {{la-IPA|pāsta|ann=1}}\n* {{la-IPA|pāstā|ann=1}}\n\n====Participle====\n{{head|la|participle form|head=pāsta}}\n\n# {{inflection of|la|pāstus||nom//voc|f|s|;|nom//acc//voc|n|p|t=fed, nourished; having eaten, consumed; grazed, pastured; satisfied, gratified}}\n\n====Participle====\n{{head|la|participle form|head=pāstā}}\n\n# {{inflection of|la|pāstus||abl|f|s|t=fed, nourished; having eaten, consumed; grazed, pastured; satisfied, gratified}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:la:L&S}}\n* {{R:la:du Cange}}\n* {{R:la:Gaffiot|page=1123}}\n* {{R:la:Georges|page=1502}}\n\n==Latvian==\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|lv|noun form|g=m}}\n\n# {{infl of|lv|pasts||gen|s}}\n\n==Malay==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{bor+|ms|en|pasta}}, from {{der|ms|it|pasta}}, from {{der|ms|la-lat|pasta|t=dough, pastry cake, paste}}, from {{der|ms|grc|παστά|t=barley porridge}}, neuter plural of {{m|grc|παστός|t=sprinkled with salt}}, from {{der|ms|grc|πάσσω||to sprinkle}}, from {{der|ms|ine-pro|*kʷeh₁t-||to shake}}. {{doublet|ms|pes}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{ms-IPA}}\n** {{audio|ms| LL-Q9237 (msa)-GinormousBuildings-pasta.wav |a=Malaysia}}\n* {{rhymes|ms|asta|ta|a|s=2|s2=2|s3=2}}\n* {{hyph|ms|pas|ta}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{ms-noun|j=ڤستا}}\n\n# {{l|en|pasta}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:PRPM}}\n\n==Mòcheno==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{bor|mhn|it|pasta}}, from {{der|mhn|la-lat|pasta}}, from {{der|mhn|grc|παστά}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{mhn-noun|f}}\n\n# [[#English|pasta]]\n\n===References===\n* {{R:CLM}}\n\n{{c|mhn|Foods}}\n\n==Norwegian Bokmål==\n{{wp|no:}}\n\n===Etymology===\nBorrowed from {{bor|nb|it|pasta}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{nb-noun-m1}}\n\n# {{lb|nb|chiefly|uncountable}} {{l|en|pasta}} {{C|nb|Foods}}\n# [[paste]]\n#: {{syn|nb|tannpasta}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:nb:OB}}\n\n==Norwegian Nynorsk==\n{{wp|nn:}}\n\n===Etymology===\nBorrowed from {{bor|nn|it|pasta}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{nn-noun-m2}}\n\n# {{lb|nn|chiefly|uncountable}} {{l|en|pasta}} {{C|nn|Foods}}\n# [[paste]]\n#: {{syn|nn|tannpasta}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:nn:OB}}\n\n==Polish==\n{{wp|pl:}}\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{pl-pr|a=LL-Q809 (pol)-Poemat-pasta.wav}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\n{{lbor|pl|la-lat|pasta}}, from {{der|pl|grc|παστά}}.\n\n====Noun====\n{{pl-noun|f}}\n\n# [[paste]] {{gl|soft mixture}}\n# [[Italian]] {{l|en|pasta}}\n\n=====Declension=====\n{{pl-decl-noun-f}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col|pl|title=nouns|pasta do butów|pasta do zębów|pasta kanapkowa|pasta ścierna|pasta termoprzewodząca}}\n{{col|pl|title=verb|pastować<g:impf>}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\n{{ety|pl|:clipping|copypasta|text=+|tree=1}}\n\n====Noun====\n{{pl-noun|f}}\n\n# {{lb|pl|Internet slang}} [[copypasta]] {{gl|block of text which has been copied and pasted from somewhere else}}\n#: {{syn|pl|copypasta}}\n\n=====Declension=====\n{{pl-decl-noun-f}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:pl:WSJP}}\n* {{R:pl:PWN}}\n\n{{C|pl|Foods|Internet memes|Italy|Pasta}}\n\n==Portuguese==\n{{wp|pt:}}\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{pt-IPA}}\n* {{rhymes|pt|astɐ|q1=Brazil|aʃtɐ|q2=Portugal|s=2}}\n* {{audio|pt|LL-Q5146 (por)-MedK1-pasta.wav|a=<<Brazil>> (<<Caipira>>)}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\n{{etymon|pt|:inh|roa-opt:pasta<id:paste>|id=paste}}\nFrom {{inh|pt|roa-opt|pasta}}, from {{inh|pt|la-lat|pasta|t=dough, pastry cake, paste}}, from {{der|pt|grc|παστά}}.\n\nCognate with {{cog|gl|pasta}}.\n\n====Noun====\n{{pt-noun|f}}\n\n# {{lb|pt|cooking}} [[dough]] {{gloss|mix of flour and other ingredients}}\n#: {{syn|pt|massa}}\n# [[paste]]\n#: {{uxi|pt|Eu gosto de escovar os dentes com essa '''pasta''' de dente.|I like to brush my teeth with this toothpaste.}}\n# [[folder]] {{gloss|organizer}}\n# {{lb|pt|computing}} [[folder]] {{gloss|container of computer files}}\n#: {{syn|pt|diretório}}\n# [[briefcase]] {{gloss|case used for carrying documents}}\n#: {{syn|pt|maleta}}\n# {{lb|pt|politics}} [[ministry]]; [[portfolio]] {{gloss|responsibilities of a government department}}\n# {{lb|pt|Portugal|slang|uncountable}} [[money]]\n#: {{syn|pt|Thesaurus:dinheiro}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col|pt|pasta dentífrica|pasta de dente|pasta de dentes|pastoso}}\n\n=====Descendants=====\n* {{desc|hrx|Pasda|bor=1}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\n{{nonlemma}}\n\n====Verb====\n{{head|pt|verb form}}\n\n# {{pt-verb form of|pastar}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:pt:Aulete}}\n* {{R:pt:Infopédia}}\n* {{R:pt:Michaelis}}\n* {{R:pt:Priberam}}\n\n{{cln|pt|terms inherited from Latin}}\n\n==Sardinian==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|sc|la-lat|pasta}}, from {{der|sc|grc|παστά}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|sc|/ˈpasta/}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{sc-noun|f|pastas}}\n\n# {{l|en|paste}}\n# [[#English|pasta]]\n# {{l|en|dough}}\n\n{{c|sc|Foods}}\n\n==Serbo-Croatian==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{sh-IPA|pȁsta}}\n* {{hyphenation|sh|pas|ta}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{sh-noun|pȁsta|f}}\n\n# [[paste]], [[polish]]\n#: {{uxi|sh|pasta za zube|toothpaste}}\n#: {{uxi|sh|pasta za cipele|shoe polish}}\n\n====Declension====\n{{sh-decl-noun\n|pȁsta|paste\n|paste|pȃstā // pȃstī\n|pasti|pastama\n|pastu|paste\n|pasto|paste\n|pasti|pastama\n|pastom|pastama\n}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{l|sh|pasta za zube}}\n* {{l|sh|pasta za cipele}}\n\n==Sicilian==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|scn|la-lat|pasta}}, from {{der|scn|grc|παστά}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|scn|/ˈpasta/|[ˈpaʃta]}}\n* {{hyphenation|scn|pàs|ta}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{scn-noun|past|f|a}}\n\n# [[#English|pasta]]\n# [[dough]]\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{l|scn|pasta asciutta}}, {{l|scn|pastasciutta}}\n* {{l|scn|sculapasta}}\n\n{{cln|scn|terms inherited from Latin}}\n{{C|scn|Foods}}\n\n==Slovak==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{bor+|sk|la-lat|pasta}}; cf. Italian {{m|it|pasta}}, English {{m|en|paste}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{sk-IPA}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{sk-noun|f|adj=pastový|dim=pastička}}\n\n# [[paste]]\n\n====Declension====\n{{sk-ndecl|f}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:sk:SDK}}\n\n{{C|sk|Foods}}\n\n==Spanish==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{es-pr|+<audio:LL-Q1321 (spa)-Millars-pasta.wav<a:Spain>>}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\n{{etymon|es|:inh|la-lat:pasta<id:food>|id=paste|tree=1}}\n{{inh+|es|la-lat|pasta}}, from {{der|es|grc|παστά}}.\n\n====Noun====\n{{es-noun|f}}\n\n# {{l|en|pasta}}\n# [[paste]], [[dough]]\n# [[biscuit]]\n# {{lb|es|Spain|slang}} [[money]], [[dough]]\n#: {{syn|es|plata<q:Latin America>|lana|dinero}}\n#* '''2006''', Irvine Welsh, Federico Corriente Basús transl., ''Porno'', Anagrama ({{ISBN|9788433938565}})\n#*: {{quote|es|No está tan engreído como de costumbre; parece bien jodido. «No lo entiendo, Spud. Pensé que me quedaba mucha '''pasta''' para las vacaciones; tenía previsto llevarme a mi hija por ahí.{{nb...}}»}}\n# {{lb|es|slang}} {{ellipsis of|es|pasta de cocaína||[[cocaine paste]]}}\n# {{ellipsis of|es|pasta de dientes||[[toothpaste]]}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col|es|hecho de otra pasta|pasta base|pasta de dientes|pasta de papel|pasta de té<t:tea-cake>|pasta para untar<qq:culinary><t:spread>}}\n\n=====Related terms=====\n{{col|es|pasto|pastar|pastor}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\n{{nonlemma}}\n\n====Verb====\n{{head|es|verb form}}\n\n# {{es-verb form of|pastar}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:es:DRAE}}\n\n{{C|es|Foods}}\n{{cln|es|terms inherited from Latin}}\n\n==Swedish==\n{{wp|sv:}}\n[[File:(Pasta) by David Adam Kess (pic.2).jpg|thumb|300px|olika sorters '''pasta''' [different types of '''pasta'''] ]]\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{audio|sv|Sv-pasta.ogg}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{sv-noun|c}}\n\n# {{l|en|pasta}}\n#: {{ux|sv|{{l|sv|koka}} '''pasta'''|cook [boil, literally] '''pasta'''}}\n# {{l|sv|paste}}\n\n====Declension====\n{{sv-infl-noun-c-or}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{l|sv|currypasta||curry paste}}\n* {{l|sv|sockerpasta||sugar paste}}\n\n====See also====\n* {{l|sv|spaghetti}}\n* {{l|sv|makaron|makaroner}}\n* {{l|sv|ketchup}}\n* {{l|sv|köttfärssås}}\n* {{l|sv|nudel}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:svenska.se|so}}\n* {{R:svenska.se|saol}}\n* {{R:svenska.se|saob}}\n\n==Tagalog==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{etymon|tl|:bor|es:pasta<id:paste>|:sl|en:paste<id:moist mixture>|:sl|en:pasta<id:food>|tree=1|id=paste}}\n{{bor+|tl|es|pasta}}, from {{der|tl|la-lat|pasta}}, from {{der|tl|grc|παστά}}.\n\n* {{s|adhesive paste}} {{sl|tl|en|paste}}. \n* {{s|pasta dish}} {{sl|tl|en|pasta}}, which came from {{der|tl|it|pasta}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{tl-pr|+,pastâ<q:obsolete><n^paste; plaster; board cover; pasta>|+,pastà,pastâ<n^filling>}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{tl-noun|b=+}}\n\n# [[dough]]; [[batter]]; [[paste]] {{gl|soft mixture used in making [[pastry]]}}\n#: {{syn|tl|masa}}\n# [[plaster]] {{gl|mixture for coating}}\n#: {{syn|tl|paletada|argamasa}}\n# {{lb|tl|colloquial}} [[adhesive]] [[paste]]\n#: {{syn|tl|pandikit|pandigkit|pandagkit|kola|engrudo}}\n# [[board]] [[cover]] {{q|in [[bookbinding]]}}\n#: {{syn|tl|pabalat|engkuwadernasyon}}\n# {{l|en|pasta}} [[dish]]\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|tl|ipasta|magpasta|pastahan}}\n\n====Related terms====\n{{col|tl|entera-pasta|medya-pasta|pastel|pasteleriya}}\n\n====See also====\n{{col|tl|pansit}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{tl-noun|+,pastà,pastâ|b=+}}\n\n# {{lb|tl|dentistry}} [[filling]]\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|tl|pastahan|pastaan}}\n\n====See also====\n{{col|tl|amalgama}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:KWF Diksiyonaryo}}\n* {{R:Pambansang Diksiyonaryo}}\n* {{R:Diccionario tagálog-hispano|1043}}\n* {{R:tl:Hispanismos 1972|page=447|q=pasta}}\n\n{{C|tl|Building materials|Foods}}\n\n==Turkish==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|tr|ota|پاسته|t=pasta|tr=pasta}}<!--Redhouse: \"various kinds of macaroni paste\"-->, borrowed from {{der|tr|it|pasta}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|tr|/pɑs.tɑ/}}\n* {{audio|tr|LL-Q256 (tur)-ToprakM-pasta.wav}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{tr-noun|yı|lar}}\n\n# {{lb|tr|cooking}} [[cake]]\n#: {{uxi|tr|Doğum günü '''pasta'''sı çok güzeldi.|The birthday '''cake''' was very nice.}}\n\n====Declension====\n{{tr-infl-noun-v|a|poss=1}}\n\n====See also====\n* {{l|tr|kek}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:ota:Redhouse|پاسته|page=433}}\n\n{{C|tr|Desserts}}\n\n==Welsh==\n{{wp|cy:}}\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{bor|cy|en|pasta}}, from {{der|cy|it|pasta}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|cy|/ˈpasda/|[ˈpʰasta]}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{cy-noun|m|-}}\n\n# [[#English|pasta]]\n\n===Mutation===\n{{cy-mut}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:cy:GPC}}\n\n{{C|cy|Foods}}\n\n==West Frisian==\n\n===Etymology===\nProbably borrowed from {{bor|fy|nl|pasta}}, from {{der|fy|it|pasta}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{fy-noun|c|pasta's}}\n\n# {{topics|fy|Foods}} [[#English|pasta]]"}}